    ('SPEA-V 185', 'MANAGEMENT OF PUBLIC PROBLEMS AND SOLUTIONS', '12290', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'PV 167', 'Deanna Malatesta', 1, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SPEA', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course introduces students to the theory, skills, and processes of management across sectors. Topics of accountability, decision making, collaborative partnerships, and social equity are highlighted in considering how managers develop solutions for increasingly difficult governance problems.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
