    ('SPEA-V 186', 'INTRODUCTION TO PUBLIC BUDGETING AND FINANCE', '9473', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 7:05 PM–8:20 PM', 'PV 169', 'Philip Lehmkuhler', 3, 'Lecture', 'Lecture', '3', 'SPEA', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The course explores the budgetary process that governs spending in the public sector. It also describes the various revenue sources available to public and non-profit sectors and the accounting documents that are used to record financial activities in the public and non-profit sectors.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
