    ('SPEA-V 261', 'USING IT IN PUBLIC AFFAIRS', '3005', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'PV 151', 'Roger Morris', 2, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'SPEA', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Course explores IT and computing in public affairs. Topics include basic IT concepts, project proposals, network and infrastructure design, security, ethics, data and document management, cloud computing, and IT futures. Applications include using office suites, website development, and building spreadsheets and statistics, and databases. Recommend basic understanding of computer operations.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
